Aldi has requested the ability to make employees work more than 38 hours a week in a submission to the Workplace Relations Productivity Commission . 
  The Transport Workers' Union National Secretary Tony Sheldon accused the supermarket chain of trying to reintroduce serfdom . 
  He said the chain was trying to 'turn the clocks back on our modern society' Aldi has previously tried to increase workers hours in 2012 but failed . 
  The supermarket chain has requested a change to the Fair Work Act . 
 